Manchester City has confirmed the team that will take on Real Madrid in the UEFA Champions League round of 16 first-leg tie at the Santiago Bernabeu on Wednesday night. The Premier League champions announced a list of 22 players to face Zinedine Zidane’s men in a post on their official website on Tuesday. Pep Guardiola’s men head to the game after beating Leicester City in the Premier League in their last encounter. Below is Man City’s squad against Real Madrid:
Kevin De Bruyne, Bernardo Silva, David Silva, Benjamin Mendy, Fernandinho, Riyad Mahrez, Joao Cancelo, Nicolas Otamendi, Ederson, Scott Carson, Phil Foden, Claudio Bravo, Kyle Walker, John Stones, Raheem Sterling, Ilkay Gundogan, Gabriel Jesus, Sergio Aguero, Oleksandr Zinchenko, Aymeric Laporte, Rodrigo and Eric Garcia. The match kick-off is at 9 pm.